 patients on track."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How does AI Scribe support in-person visits?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"During the consultation, providers can record the encounter and use AI Scribe to transcribe notes and generate consultation documents. This saves time on paperwork and ensures consistent, accurate documentation."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What documents can providers generate after an in-person consultation?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Providers can create consultation notes, prescriptions, and lab orders. Documents are automatically branded with clinic details, available in standard PDF format, and accessible to patients via their portal or mobile app."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Does the system handle billing and payments for in-person visits?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Bills are automatically generated when appointments are booked. Additional in-clinic services can be added to bills during the encounter. Patients can pay online or at the clinic, and funds are deposited directly into the clinic's account."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can new patients be onboarded for in-person visits?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Admins can register new patients easily, and nurses can complete health records before the consultation. This ensures providers have full patient context during the encounter."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How does the system handle multiple practice locations?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"For multi-location clinics, services, schedules, and documents can be defined by practice location. All encounters, documents, and billing records are automatically linked to the correct site, helping clinics stay organized."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Are notifications sent for appointments and documents?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. The system sends automated notifications for appointment confirmations, reminders, payments, an